message: Children between 12 and 14 are most at risk of becoming victims of sex trafficking in California, officials said. Many come from broken families and foster care and are seeking love and acceptance.

data.description: A statewide human trafficking sting has resulted in the rescue of 56 people, including 11 girls, officials said Tuesday. data.title: Human trafficking crackdown nets more than 500 arrests statewide
